        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-05T21:10:01Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In deciding what to do here:\n\n1. I know that Fuchsia only builds for 64-bit architectures now (namely x86-64 and arm64). Is that an ongoing guarantee, or is there a possibility that there may be a 32-bit architecture hosting Fuchsia in the future?\n\n2. Even if the answer to (1) is “32-bit is not foreclosed,” it seems that a multi-bitted Fuchsia, in which a single system might host both 64-bit and 32-bit user spaces, may never happen for other reasons. Reasonable assumption?\n\nOn the basis of the answers to these questions, we may be able to rule out cross-bitting on Fuchsia altogether. It’d be good to know this up front, since it may impact some of these existing interfaces.",
      "revId": "4337a2ee984aecf28ea5206083177a14d316d6a2",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
